{"type": "article", "id": 27207, "title": "癌症这个超级复杂的命题，被这个葡萄牙人变成了信息图", "description": "葡萄牙插画师 Cristiana Couceiro 在最近一期的《纽约时报》杂志上，用插画展现癌症的方方面面。", "date": "2016-05-23T15:26:56Z", "super_tag": "", "tags": [{"id": 155, "name": "癌症"}, {"id": 19563, "name": "插画师"}, {"id": 3253, "name": "葡萄牙"}, {"id": 2443, "name": "杂志"}, {"id": 9463, "name": "NYT Magazine"}, {"id": 28010, "name": "Cristiana Couceiro"}], "category": 17, "author": 37534, "comment_count": 3, "praise_count": 130, "image": "img/article/article_show/20160702124211EwSJq86OagmeoZPH.jpg", "contents": "\n\n<p class=\"\">5 月 15 日这一期《纽约时报》杂志，<a href=\"http://www.creativereview.co.uk/cr-blog/2016/may/cristiana-couceiro-illustrates-nyt-magazines-special-report-on-cancer/\">有一个多达 26 页的癌症专题</a>。专题的名字叫作 The New Anatomy of Cancer，介绍了与癌症有关的最新研究。在这期专题里，编辑们邀请了葡萄牙插画师<a href=\"http://www.cristianacouceiro.com\"> Cristiana Couceiro </a>绘制了癌症相关的一系列图片，这 11 幅作品涵盖了图表、插画等等，反映了癌症相关的数据和方方面面。</p>\n<div class=\"com-insert-images\">\n<figure class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160702124204tc6hW5r9absR48lN.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.75\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n<figcaption class=\"\"><div style=\"text-align: center;\">The New Anatomy of Cancer，这是《纽约时报》杂志癌症专题的封面</div></figcaption></figure><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160702124205EkPBm0IVi2M7oLF9.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.593\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n<figcaption class=\"\"><div style=\"text-align: center;\">内文插图</div></figcaption></figure>\n</div>\n<div class=\"com-insert-images\"></div>\n<div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160702124205KAeaSkq4FdfPVRwD.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.75\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n<figcaption class=\"\"><div style=\"text-align: center;\">插画师 Cristiana Couceira 的绘制风格与专题主题很契合 </div></figcaption></figure></div>\n<div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160702124206BiYnPDk1j9rHNyCx.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.75\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n<figcaption class=\"\"><div style=\"text-align: center;\">绘制患病部位</div></figcaption></figure></div>\n<div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160702124206qgpkiORy0IbY2u8a.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.75\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div>\n<div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160702124207viHgsIcQawVM0PZm.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.75\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div>\n<div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160702124207kdaYgs29ryzn6bOp.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.75\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div>\n<p>各大媒体都在讨论癌症，是因为近 30 年来，世界癌症发病率以年均 3%-5% 的速度递增，癌症已成为人类第一位死因。</p>\n<p>2000 年，世界共有癌症新发病例 1040 万，死亡病例 650 万；预计到 2030 年，这些数字将上升到新发病例 2640 万，死亡病例 1320 万。</p>\n<p>去年年初，<a href=\"http://www.infzm.com/content/114839/\">《科学》杂志发表了一篇十分有争议的论文</a>，这篇论文的作者是托马塞提（Cristian Tomasetti）和沃格尔斯坦（Bert Vogelstein）。这两位博士认为，只有不到 1/3 的癌症是环境和遗传因素所致，绝大多数人患癌症都是出于“坏运气”，即正常干细胞 DNA 复制时出现了基因突变。这个结论震惊到了很多人。</p>\n<p>去年的 12 月，另外一本顶级学术期刊《自然》发表了一篇针锋相对的文章。它认为只有 10%-30% 的癌症可以归结于基因突变，也就是所谓的“坏运气”，而近 90% 的癌症都可以追溯到病人的生活方式、环境等因素。</p>\n<div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160702124208X2FPHIOKaZWrvhgs.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.75\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div>\n<div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160702124208N39wWk5Fhl0Xa4cR.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.75\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div>\n<p class=\"\">《纽约时报》杂志之所以邀请  Cristiana Couceira 绘制插图，是因为她的创作风格鲜明。下面是她绘制的与现实相结合的题材。</p>\n<div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160702124209GeH6LrOzoBs2cMRd.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.427\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n<figcaption class=\"\"><div style=\"text-align: center;\">Cristiana Couceira  作品，Illustration for MIT Technology Review. </div></figcaption></figure></div>\n<div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160702124209PUgHGA7Szbojm3pR.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.82929399\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n<figcaption class=\"\"><div style=\"text-align: center;\">The Elusive Maggie Thatcher. Illustration for The Atlantic, review of High Dive, a book by Jonathan Lee. </div></figcaption></figure></div>\n<div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/201607021242100hEWNP8itxFVHMcm.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.41430948\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n<figcaption class=\"\"><p style=\"text-align: center;\">© cristiana couceiro</p></figcaption></figure></div>\n<div class=\"com-insert-images medium-insert-active\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/201607021242101Ykx4G8nqWczQXdp.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.69410569\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n<figcaption class=\"\"><div style=\"text-align: center;\">The President of the Cool. Illustration for The New york Times, Opinion Pages.</div></figcaption></figure></div>\n<div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160702124211QLbin06G1sfjX9tg.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.738\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div>\n<p>关于癌症，2013 年曾流行过一本名叫《众病之王：癌症传》的书。作者悉达多·穆克吉用六年时间搜集了癌症相关的翔实资料、文献和媒体报道，还做了不少患者专访。他通过这本书向读者阐述了癌症的起源与发展，介绍了人类对抗癌症的历史。想了解更多相关内容，可以去翻阅这本书。</p>\n<p class=\"\">题图来源：<a href=\"http://www.creativereview.co.uk/cr-blog/2016/may/cristiana-couceiro-illustrates-nyt-magazines-special-report-on-cancer/\">creativereview</a></p>\n\n"}